inition.lean imports to see what works. I'm noticing that both files use `open BigOperators` without explicitly importing it, which means the notation must be coming through transitive imports from the matrix modules. Since `Finset.sum` with the ∑ notation is available via `Mathlib.Algebra.BigOperators.Basic`, I should be able to rely on that being pulled in transitively from `Mathlib.Data.Matrix.Basic` rather than adding an explicit import.\n\nNow I need to verify how matrix extensionality works in Lean 4 Mathlib—specifically whether `Matrix.ext_iff` gives me the right lemma to work with, or if I need to use a different variant like `Matrix.funext_iff`.\n\nLooking at the actual definition, `Matrix.ext_iff` should provide the equivalence I need to convert between matrix equality and pointwise equality of entries. The issue might be that my current imports are pulling in conflicting definitions, so I should strip down to just what E1HDefinition uses and remove the E88Definition import that's likely causing build errors.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1061,"cache_read_input_tokens":90598,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1061},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6cd06645-8a00-4465-88a4-569f84504161","uuid":"17e1f475-e9cb-4b9f-9979-25a112fcac1e"}
