{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LTcJ5uDbdayVYJ5TqXthMA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good progress. Now I see two main issues:\n\n1. Syntax error in `all_goals` block at line 237 - the `first | ... | ...` syntax is causing issues\n2. The `simp [Matrix.of_apply] at this` after `have this := congr_fun (congr_fun h ...)` doesn't close the goal completely\n\nThe goals for the matrix distinctness are all `⊢ False`. The `have this` gives us entries that are equal, but `simp` needs to simplify them to show they're contradictory.\n\nFor case 1: `h : (of (fun i j => if i.val=0 ∧ j.val=0 then 1 else 0)) = (of (fun i j => if i.val=0 ∧ j.val=1 then 1 else 0))`\n\n\nWhen I apply `congr_fun` twice with the indices, I get an equality between the matrix entries at position (0,0), and after simplifying with `Matrix.of_apply`, the conditional expressions should reduce to `1 = 0`, which is a direct contradiction.\n\nThe issue is that my `all_goals` tactic uses `simp [Matrix.of_apply]` but doesn't fully close the goal—it gets to `1 = 0` but needs an additional step like `norm_num` to recognize this as false and discharge it automatically.\n\nI think the real problem is that my `first | ... | ...` syntax inside `all_goals` isn't working correctly, so I'll just handle each of the 6 cases individually. For each one, I'll extract the matrix entry at the specific position, simplify it with `simp [Matrix.of_apply]` to expose the contradiction, then use `norm_num` to finish it off. I'm checking the remaining pairs of basis matrices to verify they're all distinct, working through each comparison systematically to confirm none of them are equal. I'm checking whether e₀₁ and e₁₀ actually differ by testing them at (0,1), where e₀₁ gives 1 but e₁₀ gives 0. Now I need to verify that e₁₀ and e₁₁ are also distinct by comparing their outputs at (1,0).\n\nNow I'm thinking about how to structure the proof using `cong