{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KjBUotWBUvckq8r1L1RxTx","type":"tool_result","content":"    95→\n    96→/-- Helper: inner product of orthogonal basis vectors is 0.\n    97→For the standard basis vectors e₀ (= 1 at index 0, 0 elsewhere) and\n    98→e₁ (= 1 at index 1, 0 elsewhere), their inner product is 0. -/\n    99→private theorem basis_inner_product_zero (d : ℕ) (hd0 : 0 < d) (hd1 : 1 < d) :\n   100→    ∑ j : Fin d, (if j.val = 0 then (1:ℝ) else 0) * (if j.val = 1 then 1 else 0) = 0 := by\n   101→  apply Finset.sum_eq_zero\n   102→  intro j _\n   103→  split_ifs with h0 h1\n   104→  · -- j.val = 0 and j.val = 1: impossible\n   105→    exact absurd (h0.symm.trans h1) (by decide)\n   106→  · ring\n   107→  · ring\n   108→  · ring\n   109→\n   110→/-- Helper: inner product of e₀ with itself is 1. -/\n   111→private theorem basis_self_inner_product (d : ℕ) (hd0 : 0 < d) :\n   112→    ∑ j : Fin d, (if j.val = 0 then (1:ℝ) else 0) * (if j.val = 0 then 1 else 0) = 1 := by\n   113→  -- Simplify (if p then 1 else 0) * (if p then 1 else 0) = if p then 1 else 0\n   114→  have h_sq : ∀ j : Fin d, (if j.val = 0 then (1:ℝ) else 0) * (if j.val = 0 then 1 else 0) =\n   115→                             if j.val = 0 then 1 else 0 := fun j => by split_ifs <;> ring\n   116→  simp_rw [h_sq]\n   117→  -- Convert j.val = 0 condition to j = ⟨0, hd0⟩ for Fin d\n   118→  have h_conv : ∀ j : Fin d, (if j.val = 0 then (1:ℝ) else 0) = if j = ⟨0, hd0⟩ then 1 else 0 :=\n   119→    fun j => by simp [Fin.ext_iff]\n   120→  simp_rw [h_conv]\n   121→  -- Apply sum_ite_eq: ∑ j in univ, if j = a then f j else 0 = if a ∈ univ then f a else 0\n   122→  simp [Finset.sum_ite_eq]\n   123→\n   124→/-- **THEOREM 3: E88 supports S·q content-based retrieval that E1H cannot**\n   125→\n   126→We formally demonstrate E88's content-addressable retrieval by constructing:\n   127→- A state S = e₀ ⊗ e₀ᵀ (outer product of the first standard basis vector)\n   128→- Two queries e₀ ≠ e₁ (orthogonal basis vectors)\n   129→- S · e₀ = e₀ (nonzero: retrieves the stored association)\n   130→- S · e₁ = 0   (zero: orthogonal query finds nothing)\n   131→\n   132→So different queries retrieve different information from the same state.\n   133→\n   134→**Why E1H cannot do this**: E1H's state is a D-vector h, not a matrix.\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6cd06645-8a00-4465-88a4-569f84504161","uuid":"e7a5dd26-3bbf-42e3-911a-b82d490125ec","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/erikg/elman-proofs/ElmanProofs/Expressivity/E88ExceedsE1HCapacity.lean","content":"\n/-- Helper: inner product of orthogonal basis vectors is 0.\nFor the standard basis vectors e₀ (= 1 at index 0, 0 elsewhere) and\ne₁ (= 1 at index 1, 0 elsewhere), their inner product is 0. -/\nprivate theorem basis_inner_product_zero (d : ℕ) (hd0 : 0 < d) (hd1 : 1 < d) :\n    ∑ j : Fin d, (if j.val = 0 then (1:ℝ) else 0) * (if j.val = 1 then 1 else 0) = 0 := by\n  apply Finset.sum_eq_zero\n  intro j _\n  split_ifs with h0 h1\n  · -- j.val = 0 and j.val = 1: impossible\n    exact absurd (h0.symm.trans h1) (by decide)\n  · ring\n  · ring\n  · ring\n\n/-- Helper: inner product of e₀ with itself is 1. -/\nprivate theorem basis_self_inner_product (d : ℕ) (hd0 : 0 < d) :\n    ∑ j : Fin d, (if j.val = 0 then (1:ℝ) else 0) * (if j.val = 0 then 1 else 0) = 1 := by\n  -- Simplify (if p then 1 else 0) * (if p then 1 else 0) = if p then 1 else 0\n  have h_sq : ∀ j : Fin d, (if j.val = 0 then (1:ℝ) else 0) * (if j.val = 0 then 1 else 0) =\n                             if j.val = 0 then 1 else 0 := fun j => by split_ifs <;> ring\n  simp_rw [h_sq]\n  -- Convert j.val = 0 condition to j = ⟨0, hd0⟩ for Fin d\n  have h_conv : ∀ j : Fin d, (if j.val = 0 then (1:ℝ) else 0) = if j = ⟨0, hd0⟩ then 1 else 0 :=\n    fun j => by simp [Fin.ext_iff]\n  simp_rw [h_conv]\n  -- Apply sum_ite_eq: ∑ j in univ, if j = a then f j else 0 = if a ∈ univ then f a else 0\n  simp [Finset.sum_ite_eq]\n\n/-- **THEOREM 3: E88 supports S·q content-based retrieval that E1H cannot**\n\nWe formally demonstrate E88's content-addressable retrieval by constructing:\n- A state S = e₀ ⊗ e₀ᵀ (outer product of the first standard basis vector)\n- Two queries e₀ ≠ e₁ (orthogonal basis vectors)\n- S · e₀ = e₀ (nonzero: retrieves the stored association)\n- S · e₁ = 0   (zero: orthogonal query finds nothing)\n\nSo different queries retrieve different information from the same state.\n\n**Why E1H cannot do this**: E1H's state is a D-vector h, not a matrix.","numLines":40,"startLine":95,"totalLines":284}}}
