{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SzvyYpMw246zhdUuWBs5k2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Task complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Task: Prove E88 matrix state strictly exceeds E1H vector state\n\n**Created:** `ElmanProofs/Expressivity/E88ExceedsE1HCapacity.lean`\n\n**All 4 required theorems proven (no `sorry`):**\n\n1. **`e88_capacity_d_squared`** — E88 head state has D² degrees of freedom: `Fintype.card (Fin d × Fin d) = d * d` (proved by `simp`)\n\n2. **`e1h_capacity_d`** — E1H head state has D degrees of freedom: `Fintype.card (Fin d) = d` (trivial)\n\n3. **`e88_addressable_e1h_not`** — E88 supports S·q content-based retrieval that E1H cannot: Constructs S = e₀⊗e₀ᵀ and shows S·e₀ = 1 ≠ 0 = S·e₁ for orthogonal queries e₀, e₁\n\n4. **`capacity_separation`** — For d ≥ 2, E88 state scalars per head (d²) > E1H state scalars per head (d): delegates to `E1H.e88_state_exceeds_e1h_state`\n\n**Also includes:** `total_capacity_separation`, `capacity_factor`, `four_distinct_e88_states_d2`, and a `e88_exceeds_e1h_capacity_summary` combining all results.\n\n**Build result:** ✔ Zero errors, zero warnings."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":221,"cache_read_input_tokens":146061,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":221},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6cd06645-8a00-4465-88a4-569f84504161","uuid":"73addd06-744e-4c16-85ef-a62c001c72f7"}
